# Heritage Philippines V3 — Web Application Environment Variables
#
# This file is a template only: copy it to .env.local (gitignored) and
# fill in real local values as variables are introduced. Never commit
# real secrets, connection strings, tokens, or domains — only this
# .env.example template is tracked in git (see .gitignore).
#
# No environment variables are required by this foundational scaffold yet.
# Each future variable is added here only when the feature that needs it
# is actually implemented (never in advance), together with:
#   - its purpose,
#   - whether it's server-only or browser-exposed (NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix),
#   - and whether it's required in local, staging, and production.
#
# Full naming, isolation, and secret-handling strategy — including the
# server-only vs. NEXT_PUBLIC_ rule, secret generation/rotation/exposure
# response, and the database/auth/email/storage boundaries — is defined
# in docs/HERITAGE_V3_ENVIRONMENT_CONFIGURATION.md. See that document
# before adding a new variable here.
